						<summary>

						<p>Slab in survey No. 1770, east of the village.</p>						

						<p>Rēnāṭi chōḷa: Mahīchōḷa.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 9th century A.D., On the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land at Vēḷpucheṟuvu along with its tax-incomes by Karikāla chōḷa Kaṟsavēṁgu, a sub-ordinate of the king, while ruling over Vēḷpucheṟuvu.</p>						

